            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">Copy.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p>At a meeting of the Congregation Keneseth<lb/> Israel, held <date>April 17<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date>, at the<lb/> Committee rooms, in
                    <placeName>New Market<lb/> Street, above Noble</placeName>, the following
                pre-<lb/>amble and resolutions were proposed<lb/> and unanimously adopted:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Whereas, On the occasion of the<lb/> consecration of our new
                Synagogue we<lb/> have derived such great benefit from various Gentlemen, on whose
                kindness<lb/> and assistance we had no other claim<lb/> than that of charity, that
                we deem it<lb/> expedient and proper to express our<lb/> thanks to them in this
                manner.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Be it therefore. Resolved. That<lb/> the thanks of the congregation
                are<lb/> due, to the <persName>Rev. Isaac Leeser</persName>, for<lb/> the excellent
                sermon which he delivered<lb/> on the occasion, to the <persName>Rev.
                    Fraenkel</persName>,<lb/>
                <persName>Rev. S. Morais</persName>, <persName>Rev. Pope</persName> and
                    <persName>Rev.<lb/> Fassbender</persName> for the services they so</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>kindly volunteered and so ably performed;<lb/> and also to the <persName>Rev. L.
                    Naumburg</persName><lb/> for the exertions he used in rendering<lb/> the
                ceremonies worthy of the praise<lb/> and admiration of those who<lb/> participated
                in them.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved. That we tender our<lb/> sincere thanks to the
                Presidents<lb/> and Committees of the Congregations<lb/> „Beth Elohim” „Beth
                Israel”<lb/> and „Rodef Sholom” for the favors<lb/> which they accorded with such
                good<lb/> will and at so short a notice; and<lb/> also to <persName>Messrs. Jacob
                    Langsdorf</persName>,<lb/>
                <persName>Josep Einstein</persName>, <persName>Allen</persName>,
                    <persName>Henry<lb/> Mayer</persName>, <persName>M. Goldsmith</persName>,
                    <persName>Jacob<lb/> Mayer</persName> and other gentlemen who<lb/> aided in the
                management. Also<lb/> to <persName>Professors Fisher</persName> and
                    <persName>Sherrer</persName><lb/> for the skillful manner in which<lb/> they
                conducted the musical arrange<lb/>ments; to the ladies and gentlemen of the<lb/>
                choir and to <persName>Messrs. Shoemaker &amp; Co.</persName> for their</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>kind loan of a melodeon, and to all others<lb/> who, though, their names may not
                be<lb/> mentioned here, have assisted in the cere-<lb/>monies.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved. That a copy of these<lb/> resolutions be sent to each of
                the reverend<lb/> gentlemen and others herein mentioned,<lb/> and that they be
                inserted for publication<lb/> in the Ledger, Daily Register, Freie<lb/> Heimath and
                Democrat.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Weidnitzer</persName>, Secr.</p>
